# Vehicle Compatibility — local-only until explicit release

The Vehicle Compatibility List is a **separate** feature from guide management and from normal website updates.

## Never include in routine commits or pushes

Do **NOT** stage, commit, or push Vehicle Compatibility work when the user asks to:

- commit / push a "website update"
- `git add .` / commit "the changes"
- deploy, open a PR, or sync with GitHub/Vercel for general site work

Only include Vehicle Compatibility files when the user **explicitly** says to push/commit/release the **compatibility list** (or vehicle compatibility feature) by name.

## Files in scope (do not auto-commit/push)

- `src/lib/vehicle-compatibility.ts`
- `src/lib/vehicle-compatibility-actions.ts` (if present)
- `src/components/admin/vehicle-compatibility-manager.tsx`
- `src/app/(staff)/compatibility/**`
- `src/app/dealer/compatibility/**`
- `src/app/api/compatibility/**`
- `src/components/compatibility/**`
- `scripts/seed-vehicle-compatibility.ts`
- Prisma migration folders whose name contains `vehicle_compatibility`
- Compatibility-related edits inside `prisma/schema.prisma` (`VehicleCompatibility` model only)
- Compatibility tab wiring in `src/app/(staff)/users/page.tsx` and nav links for `/compatibility`
- Related `package.json` script entries such as `compat:seed`

Also respect `.git/info/exclude` entries for these paths when present.

## Product invariants

- Compatibility records must **never** create, edit, delete, publish, unpublish, or modify guides or guide content.
- Optional `sourceGuideId` is read-only provenance only — not a control channel for guides.
- Dealer / public / API compatibility views **omit** rows whose linked source guide is `ARCHIVED`, or whose guide has `hideFromCompatibility` (guide-level checkbox; overrides published). Admin compatibility management may still show them.
- Prefer testing this feature locally before any release push.
